quran[7]{c,v,t,f}:
  15,1,"Alif. Lam. Ra'. These are the verses of the Book, and a Clear Qur'an.",footnotes:178624:1
  15,2,"Soon will the time come when the unbelievers will wish they were Muslims."
  15,3,"Leave them to eat and enjoy life and let false hopes amuse them. They will soon come to know."
  15,4,"Whenever We destroyed a town, a definite term had previously been decreed for it.",footnotes:178625:1
  15,5,"No people can outstrip the term for its destruction nor can it delay it."
  15,6,"They say: "O you to whom the Admonition has been revealed, you are surely crazed.",footnotes:178626:1
  15,7,"Why do you not bring down angels upon us if you are indeed truthful?""
  15,8,"We do not send down the angels (in frivolity); and when We do send them down, We do so with Truth; then people are granted no respite.",footnotes:178627:1,footnotes:178628:2
  15,9,"As for the Admonition, indeed it is We Who have revealed it and it is indeed We Who are its guardians.",footnotes:178629:1
  15,10,"(O Muhammad), certainly We did send Messengers before you among the nations which have gone by."